&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;Establish strong relationships with internal team members by providing the Account Management team with clear and concise direction for the successful execution of campaigns. &lt;br&gt;•&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;Partner with your Account Manager to provide exceptional customer service and contract fulfillment. &lt;br&gt;•&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;Strategically utilize Matrix and station CRM to manage day-to-day activity, pipeline, and forecasts.&lt;br&gt;•&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;Positively and professionally represent the media group to the community at events and surrounding businesses.&lt;br&gt;What You Need:&lt;br&gt;•&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;1 to 3 years of account engagement in a professional, fast-paced media sales environment. &lt;br&gt;•&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;Proven track record of successfully achieving or exceeding sales goals and developing new business opportunities as a seller.&lt;br&gt;•&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;Established knowledge of marketing solutions including broadcasting and digital advertising including audio and interactive, and be a perpetual learner, eager to continuously expand your knowledge.&lt;br&gt;•&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;Prior working experience using Microsoft Office Suite and CRM (Client Relationship Management) systems, and ability to leverage technology to project manage workload and achieve goals.&lt;br&

